Players from Orlando Magic, Denver Nuggets &amp; Portland Trail Blazers will all touch down in SA in August to take part in the NBA Africa Game. MELROSE ARCH - The National Basketball Association (NBA) is set to return to South Africa in August for another edition of the NBA Africa Game.The inaugural NBA match, which took place in 2015, was a sell-out, breaking new ground on African soil.The match will once again follow a team Africa versus team world format. Players from Orlando Magic, Denver Nuggets and Portland Trail Blazers will all touch down in South Africa to take part in the game which will see proceeds go towards Unicef as well as the Nelson Mandela Children s Foundation.The star-studded match, which has aptly been unveiled on Africa Day, will look to continue growing the sport across the continent.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)